# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NO SERVER API KEYS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This app is bring-your-own-key (BYOK). Each visitor enters their own
# Gemini / OpenRouter / custom key in the in-app Settings (gear icon).
# Keys live only in that user's browser localStorage and are sent with
# each request — they are never stored on the server or in this file.
#
# Do NOT put real API keys here. Do NOT commit .env.local.
# GEMINI_API_KEY / OPENAI_API_KEY env vars are intentionally unused.

# Optional: public site URL for docs / OAuth callbacks only (not for AI keys)
# APP_URL="https://your-deployment.example.com"

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DATAFORSEO API (optional — preferred way is through the Settings UI)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Most users should enter credentials in the app Settings (gear icon).
# These env vars are ONLY for self-hosted server deployments where you
# want a shared DataForSEO account for all users.
#
# Sign up free (no card): https://app.dataforseo.com/register
# Free $1 credit included (~500 queries).
# After that: ~$0.03 per full analysis.
#
# DATAFORSEO_LOGIN="your@email.com"
# DATAFORSEO_PASSWORD="your-auto-generated-api-password"
#
# To set these permanently for a self-hosted deployment, copy this file
# to .env.local (which is gitignored), uncomment and fill in the values.
# The app will verify credentials on first use via /api/seo/test-credentials.
#
# cp .env.example .env.local   # then edit .env.local with your real credentials
